HEADWORD: Preignition
<hw>Pre`ig*ni"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Engin.)</fld>
<def>Ignition in an internal-combustion engine while the inlet valve is
open or before compression is completed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

